—ЩXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-06-03-nushell_0_94_2.mdЩ@b705668a482999694d50175a3dd2d58746c828ff2b9d1af40827e22a4c8f3477өtitle: Nushell 0.94.2‘Ў]Ъ=[link: #table-of-content] After the last release, external commands on Windows would incorrectly interpret backslashes in their path as escape sequences despite being unquoted, for example:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
alias curl = c:\msys64\clangarm64\bin\curl.exe
               в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
                              в•°в”Җв”Җ unrecognized escape after '\' in string

```
This is now fixed by 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13027] #13027
 and externals should work correctly.
’җҗЪkTitle: title: Nushell 0.94.2
Path: ]
Content:
[link: #table-of-content] After the last release, external commands on Windows would incorrectly interpret backslashes in their path as escape sequences despite being unquoted, for example:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
alias curl = c:\msys64\clangarm64\bin\curl.exe
               в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
                              в•°в”Җв”Җ unrecognized escape after '\' in string

```
This is now fixed by 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13027] #13027
 and externals should work correctly.
—ЩXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-06-03-nushell_0_94_2.mdЩ@f6ea743aefecbb5df65408ef7a445e307a17c89199453c74161559118a464f90өtitle: Nushell 0.94.2‘Ў]ЩМ[link: #table-of-content] [link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13028] #13028
 fixes a bug when an unquoted tilde wasn't expanded properly to the home directory when being a subject of globbing.
